1
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:36,160
<i>Waited so long</i>
<i>My heart unwavering and full</i>

2
00:02:36,240 --> 00:02:39,080
This song is what made
Onanong Wongwichian famous.

3
00:02:39,880 --> 00:02:41,320
She's the ex-lover of Kamnan Pong.

4
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:42,720
PREVIOUS EPISODE

5
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:44,240
DARATHONG COUNTRY MUSIC SINGING CONTEST

6
00:02:46,560 --> 00:02:50,160
<i>He's forgotten</i>

7
00:02:51,960 --> 00:02:53,800
Even without music,

8
00:02:53,880 --> 00:02:56,120
Poona's voice still captivates everyone.

9
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:59,960
The winner is Poona,
with the song "Wait for Him to Forget."

10
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:03,040
Wow!

11
00:03:03,120 --> 00:03:05,240
Who the hell are you?

12
00:03:05,320 --> 00:03:08,400
Chart just confirmed it's really Phupha.

13
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:11,600
If you're going to blame someone,
blame your father.

14
00:03:11,680 --> 00:03:13,000
Oh no!

15
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:14,440
Both of you!

16
00:03:21,760 --> 00:03:23,840
Sorry, I didn't mean to.

17
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:28,240
You didn't mean to,
but it hit me right on the head.

18
00:03:30,320 --> 00:03:32,760
By the way, you sang
really well last night.

19
00:03:33,320 --> 00:03:35,160
I was so nervous watching you.

20
00:03:35,240 --> 00:03:37,960
You were at the competition?

21
00:03:38,040 --> 00:03:41,160
Yes, I was cheering for you
right at the edge of the stage.

22
00:03:41,760 --> 00:03:44,000
But too bad you didn't win.

23
00:03:48,240 --> 00:03:51,560
Oh my God! Hold on! Don't tell me

24
00:03:51,640 --> 00:03:53,960
you're a fan of Miss Maria.

25
00:03:54,560 --> 00:03:56,000
How cute!

26
00:03:56,080 --> 00:03:57,320
That's right.

27
00:03:58,240 --> 00:04:01,400
You'll always be my favorite singer.

28
00:04:01,480 --> 00:04:03,040
Can I be your fan?

29
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:06,880
Sure.

30
00:04:08,080 --> 00:04:09,800
- Sophie.
- Huh?

31
00:04:10,480 --> 00:04:12,000
- Sophie, Joey!
- She's calling.

32
00:04:12,080 --> 00:04:13,680
- Come here.
- Coming.

33
00:04:15,080 --> 00:04:16,079
Yes?

34
00:04:17,360 --> 00:04:18,519
Isn't he a bit of a creep?

35
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:21,240
Oh please, creeps aren't usually
this good looking!

36
00:04:21,320 --> 00:04:22,480
- Really?
- You're overthinking it.

37
00:04:27,120 --> 00:04:28,680
We're going to head out first.

38
00:04:32,120 --> 00:04:34,600
- I accidentally bumped into you.
- Look at you!

39
00:04:34,680 --> 00:04:35,760
- I didn't mean to.
- Good luck, Miss Maria!

40
00:04:35,840 --> 00:04:37,760
I'm cheering for you.

41
00:04:37,840 --> 00:04:39,560
- Bye!
- Bye!

42
00:04:40,960 --> 00:04:42,600
She's so cute.

43
00:04:45,600 --> 00:04:48,240
I've been looking for you everywhere.
You're here flirting with a girl.

44
00:04:48,320 --> 00:04:50,320
The girl here is cute
and worth flirting with.

45
00:04:50,400 --> 00:04:52,760
Let's put love aside
and focus on work, alright?

46
00:04:53,360 --> 00:04:54,600
What's up?

47
00:04:55,400 --> 00:04:57,880
Captain Tom found a lead
on the drug smugglers.

48
00:05:09,120 --> 00:05:10,200
Where is Captain Chaiya?

49
00:05:10,840 --> 00:05:13,960
I'll take care of this small task.
No need to bother the captain.

50
00:05:14,040 --> 00:05:16,560
You think you can handle it?
I don't trust you.

51
00:05:16,640 --> 00:05:18,440
Come on! I'm your nephew.

52
00:05:19,160 --> 00:05:21,280
I'm a lieutenant,
not some random guy picked by a lottery.

53
00:05:21,880 --> 00:05:23,440
Oh, you're acting so sensitive.

54
00:05:23,520 --> 00:05:25,680
Your head's not even bald.

55
00:05:26,440 --> 00:05:27,680
Hey, over there.

56
00:05:29,240 --> 00:05:30,160
What are they loading?

57
00:05:31,280 --> 00:05:32,440
Someone's watching us!

58
00:05:38,840 --> 00:05:41,840
Let's get out of here, Uncle.
Join up with Chaiya.

59
00:05:41,920 --> 00:05:43,120
Let's go!

60
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:44,320
Hurry up!

61
00:05:48,080 --> 00:05:51,240
DARATHONG MUSIC

62
00:06:07,240 --> 00:06:08,360
- Chit.
- Yes?

63
00:06:08,440 --> 00:06:09,600
You guys stay here for now.

64
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:11,440
Got it.

65
00:06:18,040 --> 00:06:20,040
You keep an eye on the car.
We'll be back soon.

66
00:06:20,120 --> 00:06:20,960
Yes.

67
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:21,960
Let's go.

68
00:06:24,720 --> 00:06:26,080
Why did they come here, Uncle?

69
00:06:26,640 --> 00:06:29,680
I don't know either.
They started loading stuff into the car

70
00:06:29,760 --> 00:06:30,960
and then came here.

71
00:06:31,640 --> 00:06:33,440
- Maybe word got out?
- That's possible.

72
00:06:33,520 --> 00:06:35,400
As soon as Captain Tom
went back to the station

73
00:06:35,480 --> 00:06:36,520
to request a search warrant,

74
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:38,800
they started packing the car
and brought everything here.

75
00:06:39,720 --> 00:06:41,680
Captain Tom still doesn't have
the search warrant?

76
00:06:41,760 --> 00:06:45,160
Not yet. He needs to go to the city
to get the warrant from the court.

77
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:48,680
Did you call Captain Tom?

78
00:06:49,280 --> 00:06:50,560
I already did.

79
00:06:57,440 --> 00:06:59,960
I think I have an idea. Wait here.

80
00:07:18,080 --> 00:07:19,200
You ready, buddy?

81
00:07:20,040 --> 00:07:21,760
Ready or not, I have to do it.

82
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:27,880
Sneak a peek inside the car,
see what's there, and take a photo.

83
00:07:29,200 --> 00:07:30,560
You can count on me.

84
00:07:37,560 --> 00:07:38,600
What's so funny, Uncle?

85
00:08:27,720 --> 00:08:29,000
What are you doing?

86
00:08:29,840 --> 00:08:33,400
I'm about to go to the market,
just opening up the GPS.

87
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:36,400
- The market's that way.
- Which way?

88
00:08:36,480 --> 00:08:37,799
Go out, go straight.

89
00:08:37,880 --> 00:08:39,200
- This way!
- Oh.

90
00:08:39,880 --> 00:08:42,320
- Go!
- You're really nice.Thank you so much!

91
00:08:42,400 --> 00:08:44,600
Go ahead. Take a left.

92
00:08:48,560 --> 00:08:50,040
Is he really blind?

93
00:08:52,880 --> 00:08:54,240
It's Captain Tom.

94
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:59,200
I heard he's searching the warehouse,
so I'm hiding the stuff here first.

95
00:09:02,320 --> 00:09:03,880
Then we have to be extra careful.

96
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:05,400
Don't let anyone find out.

97
00:09:09,560 --> 00:09:11,680
Don't worry about that, Singha.

98
00:09:12,320 --> 00:09:14,040
I've got it covered. Okay?

99
00:09:27,440 --> 00:09:28,880
Is anyone following us?

100
00:09:30,640 --> 00:09:33,560
- No one's following us, sir.
- Let's hope it stays that way.

101
00:09:34,560 --> 00:09:36,360
Otherwise, it'll cause trouble
for everyone.

102
00:09:50,720 --> 00:09:51,760
What are they carrying?

103
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:54,640
It's chemicals imported from abroad.

104
00:09:54,720 --> 00:09:57,320
What kind of chemicals? Drugs?

105
00:09:57,400 --> 00:09:58,360
No.

106
00:09:58,960 --> 00:10:01,240
It's in English, but it's not drugs.

107
00:10:01,320 --> 00:10:02,320
That's odd.

108
00:10:03,160 --> 00:10:04,440
Right.

109
00:10:05,040 --> 00:10:07,320
What are they doing with these chemicals?

110
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:11,400
Exactly. A lot of these people
are involved in drugs.

111
00:10:11,480 --> 00:10:14,040
But they're transporting chemicals,
not drugs.

112
00:10:14,680 --> 00:10:15,960
It feels strange.

113
00:10:16,040 --> 00:10:19,400
There are more chemicals in the car,
but I couldn't take pictures of it all.

114
00:10:29,240 --> 00:10:30,520
Yes, Captain.

115
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:31,600
Yes.

116
00:10:32,200 --> 00:10:35,200
Captain Tom said
that Superintendent Samuejai

117
00:10:35,280 --> 00:10:37,960
went to the court to oppose
the request for a search warrant.

118
00:10:38,040 --> 00:10:40,240
See? Word really got out.

119
00:10:41,920 --> 00:10:46,360
Looks like tonight,
we'll have to go help Captain Tom.

120
00:11:16,560 --> 00:11:18,040
- Tod.
- Yes?

121
00:11:18,640 --> 00:11:19,720
Keep an eye on the goods.

122
00:11:20,480 --> 00:11:22,760
I need to use the bathroom.
My stomach's killing me.

123
00:11:22,840 --> 00:11:24,280
Take your time.

124
00:11:24,880 --> 00:11:26,880
- Watch it closely.
- No rush.

125
00:11:26,960 --> 00:11:28,440
I don't know what you ate.

126
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:40,360
The goods should be in that room.

127
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:45,080
- What now? Should I take care of it?
- Yeah, go ahead.

128
00:12:00,960 --> 00:12:03,040
How much longer
are you going to stretch? Let's go!

129
00:12:03,720 --> 00:12:05,520
Alright, just wait and see.

130
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:06,560
Yeah.

131
00:12:17,320 --> 00:12:19,480
Hey, who are you?

132
00:12:23,160 --> 00:12:25,240
I'm asking, who are you?

133
00:12:26,720 --> 00:12:27,720
I'm your father.

134
00:12:28,560 --> 00:12:30,480
- You little bastard.
- Don't you recognize me, son?

135
00:12:46,200 --> 00:12:47,760
I haven't even broken a sweat yet.

136
00:12:49,720 --> 00:12:51,840
Already knocked out? How pathetic.

137
00:12:57,200 --> 00:12:59,960
Who the hell are you?
What are you doing here?

138
00:13:01,320 --> 00:13:04,000
- Turn around.
- I'm here to fix the air conditioner.

139
00:13:05,440 --> 00:13:08,360
You wanna die, huh? I'll make that happen.

140
00:13:18,680 --> 00:13:19,760
You better be careful.

141
00:13:19,840 --> 00:13:22,360
If you don't want to die, drop the gun.

142
00:13:43,360 --> 00:13:46,400
Hurry up and get the sample
before the security guards show up.

143
00:14:16,400 --> 00:14:17,320
- Got it.
- Okay.

144
00:14:18,760 --> 00:14:19,640
Let's go.

145
00:14:25,600 --> 00:14:27,360
How's everything? All good?

146
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:42,200
You bastard!

147
00:14:43,280 --> 00:14:44,160
Go check it out!

148
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:52,640
Get them! Go!

149
00:14:52,720 --> 00:14:53,560
Yes, sir!

150
00:14:57,360 --> 00:14:58,520
Who the hell are you?

151
00:15:34,520 --> 00:15:35,440
Where did they go?

152
00:15:48,480 --> 00:15:49,880
You're dead.

153
00:15:56,680 --> 00:15:57,680
Damn it!

154
00:16:07,520 --> 00:16:09,960
Sir, someone broke into the storage room.

155
00:16:10,040 --> 00:16:12,280
- Who are they?
- I don't know, sir.

156
00:16:14,280 --> 00:16:17,680
It's fine. Forget about it.
My stuff is legal.

157
00:16:21,640 --> 00:16:23,120
Who dares to mess with me?

158
00:16:28,160 --> 00:16:29,200
Damn it!

159
00:16:32,880 --> 00:16:36,040
Even this late, he's shooting to vent,
no care for anyone.

160
00:16:36,680 --> 00:16:38,080
He's got some serious connections.

161
00:16:41,160 --> 00:16:42,160
Hey.

162
00:16:42,880 --> 00:16:44,160
How's your arm?

163
00:16:46,840 --> 00:16:49,000
- It's fine.
- Let me see.

164
00:16:53,880 --> 00:16:55,920
Don't squeeze like that. It hurts.

165
00:16:56,520 --> 00:16:57,640
I'm just kidding.

166
00:16:57,720 --> 00:17:00,400
- Don't touch me.
- Come on, let me treat your wound.

167
00:17:00,480 --> 00:17:01,760
- Let's go.
- Ouch.

168
00:17:01,840 --> 00:17:04,520
Sorry, buddy. Let me take care of that.
I won't touch it again.

169
00:17:04,599 --> 00:17:05,839
- Let's go.
- You're such a pain.

170
00:17:11,319 --> 00:17:14,720
Do you know who the people are
who broke in last night?

171
00:17:15,280 --> 00:17:16,920
I don't have any leads yet.

172
00:17:17,520 --> 00:17:20,960
DARATHONG MUSIC

173
00:17:24,040 --> 00:17:25,800
In that case, inform the security guards

174
00:17:26,560 --> 00:17:28,560
to increase patrols during the night.

175
00:17:29,240 --> 00:17:31,320
Got it. Also, Boss,

176
00:17:31,960 --> 00:17:33,680
I shot one of them in the arm last night.

177
00:17:36,680 --> 00:17:39,160
Then, check the hospitals

178
00:17:39,240 --> 00:17:42,440
and clinics. See if anyone
came in for treatment.

179
00:17:42,520 --> 00:17:43,800
Understood, sir.

180
00:17:45,800 --> 00:17:47,200
Excuse me.

181
00:17:48,720 --> 00:17:51,520
The contest-winning singer,
Poona, has arrived.

182
00:17:51,600 --> 00:17:53,640
Have her wait in the office.

183
00:17:53,720 --> 00:17:56,000
And bring Sornrak along too.

184
00:17:57,000 --> 00:17:58,360
Yes, sir.

185
00:17:58,440 --> 00:18:00,040
DARATHONG MUSIC

186
00:18:01,160 --> 00:18:02,920
I'll handle the investigation.

187
00:18:03,720 --> 00:18:05,720
Those who like to poke the sleeping tiger,

188
00:18:06,480 --> 00:18:08,000
if they show up, we can't let them live.

189
00:18:19,800 --> 00:18:24,320
While we're waiting for my father,
Poona, you can read the contract first.

190
00:18:25,080 --> 00:18:27,120
It's okay, I trust you.

191
00:18:40,600 --> 00:18:42,560
We have to get that teddy bear,

192
00:18:43,160 --> 00:18:44,720
so we can rip off their mask.

193
00:18:52,400 --> 00:18:53,640
What are you looking at?

194
00:18:55,640 --> 00:18:56,760
The teddy bear.

195
00:18:58,440 --> 00:18:59,760
It's so cute.

196
00:19:01,360 --> 00:19:03,600
Poona is really into
collecting teddy bears.

197
00:19:03,680 --> 00:19:05,680
She can't resist hugging them.

198
00:19:05,760 --> 00:19:07,120
Oh, I see.

199
00:19:08,560 --> 00:19:10,600
Can I hug it for a moment?

200
00:19:12,280 --> 00:19:13,920
Sure, go ahead.

201
00:19:27,560 --> 00:19:30,400
It's so cute! I really want one.

202
00:19:31,840 --> 00:19:33,240
Do you want it?

203
00:19:35,680 --> 00:19:37,120
If so, I'll give it to you.

204
00:19:45,200 --> 00:19:46,160
Are you really giving it to me?

205
00:19:47,400 --> 00:19:48,400
Of course.

206
00:19:51,640 --> 00:19:53,880
Then, can I take it home?

207
00:19:56,320 --> 00:19:57,680
Not this one, though.

208
00:19:58,600 --> 00:20:01,840
I'll buy you a new one. This is my dad's,
and he's protective of it.

209
00:20:05,080 --> 00:20:07,560
Why is Mr. Singha so protective
of this teddy bear?

210
00:20:08,960 --> 00:20:10,920
Because this teddy bear…

211
00:20:13,120 --> 00:20:15,240
was bought for me by Sornrak's mother.

212
00:20:15,320 --> 00:20:17,440
I want to keep it as a memento.

213
00:20:21,280 --> 00:20:24,240
Sorry, but I don't like anyone
messing with my teddy bear.

214
00:20:27,600 --> 00:20:30,120
- Sorry, I didn't mean to.
- Have you read the contract?

215
00:20:32,080 --> 00:20:33,040
Yes, I've read it.

216
00:20:33,680 --> 00:20:34,960
Then you can sign it.

217
00:20:40,240 --> 00:20:43,920
Before I sign,
there's one thing I'd like to ask.

218
00:20:44,920 --> 00:20:45,840
What is it?

219
00:20:47,080 --> 00:20:50,840
You see, Teacher Mueangphrai
has a talent for composing songs.

220
00:20:50,920 --> 00:20:53,640
I was hoping you could invite him
to collaborate with us.

221
00:20:56,640 --> 00:20:58,360
What kind of songs has he composed?

222
00:20:58,960 --> 00:21:00,400
"Panda Bear."

223
00:21:01,120 --> 00:21:04,720
<i>Panda Bear, Panda Bear, Panda, Panda Bear!</i>

224
00:21:05,400 --> 00:21:06,480
That's enough.

225
00:21:08,040 --> 00:21:10,200
Dad, this song is really popular.

226
00:21:13,920 --> 00:21:16,480
Do you have any other popular songs?

227
00:21:16,560 --> 00:21:18,200
There aren't any other famous ones,

228
00:21:18,280 --> 00:21:21,160
but this new song for sure will be a hit.

229
00:21:22,240 --> 00:21:23,440
This one.

230
00:21:23,520 --> 00:21:28,480
<i>My dear, listen to me and I'll tell you</i>

231
00:21:28,560 --> 00:21:30,320
Enough.

232
00:21:33,600 --> 00:21:36,440
It's not that you're not good, Teacher.

233
00:21:37,040 --> 00:21:39,840
But at my record label,
we already have our own composers.

234
00:21:40,440 --> 00:21:44,040
They know exactly what kind of songs
will appeal to the label.

235
00:21:44,120 --> 00:21:46,560
- So, you're not accepting me yet?
- Not yet.

236
00:21:51,080 --> 00:21:52,480
But if you don't mind,

237
00:21:53,040 --> 00:21:57,280
you can work with us as the coordinator,
looking after the artists.

238
00:21:58,360 --> 00:22:01,000
I'll put you in charge of Poona.
How does that sound?

239
00:22:02,160 --> 00:22:04,200
That's fine. I don't mind.

240
00:22:04,280 --> 00:22:06,880
Thank you so much
for the opportunity to work with you.

241
00:22:09,800 --> 00:22:11,120
Then go ahead and sign.

242
00:22:18,400 --> 00:22:20,160
Poona, once you sign,

243
00:22:20,240 --> 00:22:21,880
you'll get the song to practice.

244
00:22:21,960 --> 00:22:23,360
It's on this thumb drive.

245
00:22:32,480 --> 00:22:33,600
This one too.

246
00:22:42,720 --> 00:22:45,960
Here, take a copy of the contract.

247
00:22:47,640 --> 00:22:49,880
- Give her the song to practice.
- Yes.

248
00:23:05,160 --> 00:23:08,640
Keep it a secret while practicing.
Don't tell anyone.

249
00:23:08,720 --> 00:23:09,720
It's confidential.

250
00:23:10,840 --> 00:23:11,920
Got it.

251
00:23:12,960 --> 00:23:16,160
Now, you're officially an artist

252
00:23:16,240 --> 00:23:17,960
with Darathong Music.

253
00:23:19,040 --> 00:23:21,640
From now on, you need
to be careful with your behavior.

254
00:23:21,720 --> 00:23:24,280
Don't do anything that could damage
the label's reputation.

255
00:23:24,360 --> 00:23:25,440
Understood?

256
00:23:27,800 --> 00:23:31,480
Thank you so much for giving me
the opportunity to follow my dream.

257
00:23:40,760 --> 00:23:41,800
Thank you so much.

258
00:23:43,040 --> 00:23:44,120
See you, Teacher.

259
00:24:13,080 --> 00:24:16,720
That envelope must be important
if they came to pick it up themselves.

260
00:24:18,440 --> 00:24:19,600
If so, it's valuable too.

261
00:24:19,680 --> 00:24:22,840
Sometimes they might have to pay
with their lives.

262
00:24:24,440 --> 00:24:27,040
But what's important
is which group they belong to.

263
00:24:27,800 --> 00:24:29,400
From their demeanor and weapons,

264
00:24:29,480 --> 00:24:31,520
they seem like hired criminals.

265
00:24:31,600 --> 00:24:34,800
I'll circle around and stop them
to find out what's in the envelope.

266
00:24:35,840 --> 00:24:39,400
Sounds good. I'll intercept
and handle Singha's people.

267
00:24:39,480 --> 00:24:40,800
Maybe we can force out some truth.

268
00:24:48,480 --> 00:24:49,600
What are you two doing here?

269
00:25:24,280 --> 00:25:25,160
Up.

270
00:25:30,000 --> 00:25:31,000
Come here.

271
00:25:33,520 --> 00:25:35,360
I really want to meet your boss.

272
00:25:36,320 --> 00:25:37,600
Who's your boss?

273
00:25:41,440 --> 00:25:43,960
Are you going to answer or not?
Answer, or you'll regret it!

274
00:25:44,040 --> 00:25:45,160
I'll answer.

275
00:25:47,000 --> 00:25:48,360
My boss is…

276
00:25:52,320 --> 00:25:53,520
Whoa!

277
00:26:50,000 --> 00:26:51,200
Let them go.

278
00:26:52,400 --> 00:26:53,720
They won't remember our faces.

279
00:26:56,600 --> 00:26:59,480
Sacrificing themselves for these scum,
don't they fear hell?

280
00:27:07,480 --> 00:27:08,640
What happened?

281
00:27:09,440 --> 00:27:11,000
Did we fail again?

282
00:27:11,080 --> 00:27:13,400
And we lost people too?

283
00:27:14,120 --> 00:27:18,080
It's not all bad. At least
our drug sample got destroyed.

284
00:27:18,720 --> 00:27:20,800
Otherwise, we'd be in big trouble.

285
00:27:23,160 --> 00:27:25,200
The interesting part is…

286
00:27:26,120 --> 00:27:28,320
some people are getting in our way.

287
00:27:28,920 --> 00:27:31,000
Who? Who are they?

288
00:27:31,080 --> 00:27:33,000
My men said they couldn't see
their faces clearly,

289
00:27:33,560 --> 00:27:35,360
but their skills were impressive.

290
00:27:42,760 --> 00:27:45,440
Have last night's chemical samples
been tested yet?

291
00:27:45,520 --> 00:27:46,480
They've been sent.

292
00:27:46,560 --> 00:27:49,400
When will we know the results?
Will we have them by this afternoon?

293
00:27:49,480 --> 00:27:51,680
You're so impatient. Just wait a bit.

294
00:27:57,400 --> 00:27:58,640
Hold on.

295
00:28:01,280 --> 00:28:02,120
What's up, Lieutenant?

296
00:28:04,400 --> 00:28:05,320
Okay.

297
00:28:06,200 --> 00:28:07,280
Thanks a lot.

298
00:28:09,040 --> 00:28:10,080
What is it?

299
00:28:11,240 --> 00:28:13,040
The chemical we sent for testing

300
00:28:13,760 --> 00:28:16,880
is a cleaning agent,
not something illegal.

301
00:28:16,960 --> 00:28:19,520
But they're not a cleaning company.

302
00:28:20,200 --> 00:28:23,160
Why would they order
so much of this chemical?

303
00:28:24,120 --> 00:28:26,680
Besides being a cleaning agent,

304
00:28:26,760 --> 00:28:29,720
this chemical is also a precursor
for making drugs.

305
00:28:32,880 --> 00:28:34,640
So that's what this is about.

306
00:28:38,360 --> 00:28:39,400
Teacher.

307
00:28:39,480 --> 00:28:42,880
I'm really going to be a singer now.
This isn't just a dream, right?

308
00:28:42,960 --> 00:28:45,520
Want me to slap you
to make sure you're not dreaming?

309
00:28:45,600 --> 00:28:46,960
No, thanks! It'll hurt.

310
00:28:47,560 --> 00:28:49,040
Oh, I'm just joking.

311
00:28:49,120 --> 00:28:50,840
I'm only teasing the new artist.

312
00:28:51,480 --> 00:28:53,240
- I won't really slap you.
- Wait.

313
00:28:53,320 --> 00:28:54,440
What?

314
00:28:56,200 --> 00:28:57,640
I'm so curious.

315
00:28:57,720 --> 00:29:00,200
What's the song on the flash drive?

316
00:29:00,280 --> 00:29:02,480
Hey, this is really important.

317
00:29:02,560 --> 00:29:04,840
Don't lose it.

318
00:29:04,920 --> 00:29:06,920
If you do, it'll be a big problem.

319
00:29:08,120 --> 00:29:09,360
Keep it safe, right now!

320
00:29:18,920 --> 00:29:19,960
Yay!

321
00:29:20,640 --> 00:29:23,800
I'm really going to be a singer now!

322
00:29:53,040 --> 00:29:54,200
Ouch! Hey!

323
00:29:55,000 --> 00:29:57,720
Hey! Why are you hitting me?

324
00:29:57,800 --> 00:30:00,480
Why did you press your cheek
against my lips?

325
00:30:00,560 --> 00:30:01,760
Hey, it's you!

326
00:30:01,840 --> 00:30:03,800
You kissed my cheek!

327
00:30:04,400 --> 00:30:06,440
I'm at a loss here.

328
00:30:06,520 --> 00:30:08,240
Every time we meet,
we bump into each other.

329
00:30:08,320 --> 00:30:09,400
Did a ghost push us together?

330
00:30:10,560 --> 00:30:11,840
A ghost pushed you together
to fall in love?

331
00:30:13,120 --> 00:30:14,400
- Are you crazy?
- Are you crazy?

332
00:30:22,640 --> 00:30:23,520
You signed the contract.

333
00:30:24,760 --> 00:30:28,360
Congratulations, Poona Darathong.

334
00:30:31,040 --> 00:30:32,440
Take it.

335
00:30:32,520 --> 00:30:33,760
Thanks.

336
00:30:35,840 --> 00:30:39,240
Let's go, Manat.
If we stay here, I might get hurt again.

337
00:30:39,960 --> 00:30:41,240
Wait a minute.

338
00:30:41,960 --> 00:30:43,120
What now?

339
00:30:45,400 --> 00:30:47,880
I just want to say thank you
for the competition.

340
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:52,600
If you hadn't helped me,
I probably would've been disqualified.

341
00:30:58,480 --> 00:30:59,680
It's nothing.

342
00:31:02,080 --> 00:31:02,920
Let's go.

343
00:31:04,760 --> 00:31:06,880
Why do you have to act cool?
I shouldn't have thanked you.

344
00:31:08,160 --> 00:31:09,520
Really suits you.

345
00:31:12,440 --> 00:31:13,840
What suits me, Teacher?

346
00:31:13,920 --> 00:31:16,600
Don't tell me you're talking
about me and that guy.

347
00:31:16,680 --> 00:31:19,440
Hey, I don't see how
we suit each other, Teacher!

348
00:31:19,520 --> 00:31:22,920
No, I mean the name Poona Darathong.

349
00:31:24,480 --> 00:31:27,320
It's easy to remember, easy to call.
You should become famous easily.

350
00:31:28,440 --> 00:31:30,040
- Really, Teacher?
- Hm.

351
00:31:30,680 --> 00:31:33,040
Now you've made me feel all nervous.

352
00:31:33,600 --> 00:31:35,960
Don't get excited yet.
Let me teach you the song first.

353
00:31:36,040 --> 00:31:37,720
Let's go. Time to practice singing.

354
00:31:37,800 --> 00:31:39,160
I'll teach you now.

355
00:32:25,760 --> 00:32:28,080
<i>Who owns this famous music label?</i>

356
00:32:28,160 --> 00:32:31,760
<i>They say the boss is good looking…</i>

357
00:32:31,840 --> 00:32:33,440
Hey! What's this song?

358
00:32:33,520 --> 00:32:35,040
This is Poona's new song!

359
00:32:35,120 --> 00:32:37,800
This song is gonna be a hit.
It's gonna blow up!

360
00:32:38,480 --> 00:32:40,000
<i>I want to be famous</i>

361
00:32:40,080 --> 00:32:45,280
<i>I want to try, I want to be</i>
<i>One of the artists at this label</i>

362
00:32:45,360 --> 00:32:48,200
<i>I want to be famous</i>
<i>Can't stand it anymore.</i>

363
00:32:48,280 --> 00:32:51,800
<i>I want people</i>
<i>To scream for me at the stage</i>

364
00:32:51,880 --> 00:32:54,600
<i>Please accept me as an artist</i>

365
00:32:54,680 --> 00:32:57,880
<i>I promise I'll do well…</i>

366
00:32:57,960 --> 00:32:59,280
This won't do.

367
00:32:59,360 --> 00:33:01,240
Follow me.

368
00:33:01,320 --> 00:33:04,360
<i>I'll sign a contract for years</i>
<i>If you want me to</i>

369
00:33:05,840 --> 00:33:06,920
<i>I want to be famous--</i>

370
00:33:10,280 --> 00:33:11,480
What's that noise?

371
00:33:13,320 --> 00:33:14,480
Move, quickly!

372
00:33:28,520 --> 00:33:29,760
Are you okay, Teacher?

373
00:33:29,840 --> 00:33:31,000
It smells everywhere.

374
00:33:32,280 --> 00:33:35,400
I don't know what happened.
The fermented fish jar fell and shattered.

375
00:33:36,240 --> 00:33:37,800
Let me help you.

376
00:33:39,600 --> 00:33:41,400
Such a shame, the fermented fish.

377
00:33:49,240 --> 00:33:50,800
- Teacher.
- What?

378
00:33:50,880 --> 00:33:52,080
Is this jar of fermented fish

379
00:33:52,160 --> 00:33:53,360
ruined too?

380
00:33:53,440 --> 00:33:55,520
Looks like it's ruined.
Bring it. I'll throw it away.

381
00:34:08,639 --> 00:34:11,440
Let's go, Poona. Go back to practicing.

382
00:34:12,440 --> 00:34:15,880
This is a promotional song.
You have to sing it well

383
00:34:16,440 --> 00:34:17,280
Okay, Teacher.

384
00:34:22,159 --> 00:34:24,320
It's quiet now. They've all gone.

385
00:34:24,400 --> 00:34:26,400
I'm about to pass out!

386
00:34:27,000 --> 00:34:28,159
Why so loud?

387
00:34:30,159 --> 00:34:31,600
Get out!

388
00:34:31,679 --> 00:34:34,639
- I'm going to pass out! I can't take it!
- If you're not going, I am!

389
00:34:50,800 --> 00:34:52,159
Hey there!

390
00:34:52,920 --> 00:34:54,239
We're here again.

391
00:34:54,320 --> 00:34:56,239
Hello. What can I get for you?

392
00:34:56,320 --> 00:34:59,600
- One Americano.
- Got it. What about you, Juab?

393
00:34:59,680 --> 00:35:02,040
That one with "no" in it!

394
00:35:02,120 --> 00:35:06,600
Sure! By the way, which type
of coffee bean would you like?

395
00:35:06,680 --> 00:35:10,360
Arabica, Robusta, Excelsa,

396
00:35:10,440 --> 00:35:11,560
or Liberica?

397
00:35:11,640 --> 00:35:13,720
Well…

398
00:35:13,800 --> 00:35:15,240
The last one, something with "ca".

399
00:35:16,320 --> 00:35:17,800
Liberica.

400
00:35:19,160 --> 00:35:20,960
One shot or two shots?

401
00:35:21,040 --> 00:35:22,400
Why so many questions?

402
00:35:22,480 --> 00:35:24,080
- Yeah.
- I need coffee.

403
00:35:24,160 --> 00:35:25,600
I'm craving coffee.

404
00:35:25,680 --> 00:35:29,120
Why is ordering coffee so complicated?

405
00:35:30,040 --> 00:35:33,200
I'm not going to drink it anymore.
Too hard to order.

406
00:35:34,160 --> 00:35:35,280
Let's go.

407
00:35:37,360 --> 00:35:38,400
What's with him?

408
00:35:39,840 --> 00:35:41,320
What's up with that?

409
00:35:47,200 --> 00:35:50,680
Have you noticed that everyone
who drinks coffee at our cafe

410
00:35:50,760 --> 00:35:52,000
ends up crying?

411
00:35:53,240 --> 00:35:55,640
Because our coffee is so good, Dad.

412
00:35:56,240 --> 00:35:59,480
I was right to open this coffee shop.

413
00:36:00,760 --> 00:36:03,960
It allows the villagers
to taste the deliciousness

414
00:36:04,040 --> 00:36:05,000
at our shop.

415
00:36:06,080 --> 00:36:08,960
We're really doing a good deed.

416
00:36:09,040 --> 00:36:10,240
Yes, Dad.

417
00:36:15,760 --> 00:36:18,320
- Big news, Miss Maria!
- Big news, Village Head!

418
00:36:24,480 --> 00:36:26,600
Did you fall into a toilet or something?

419
00:36:26,680 --> 00:36:30,080
It's not a toilet, it's the fermented fish
from Mueangphrai's house.

420
00:36:30,160 --> 00:36:32,080
Yes, we risked our lives

421
00:36:32,160 --> 00:36:35,000
to gather information about them
for you, Village Head!

422
00:36:35,880 --> 00:36:36,760
What's going on?

423
00:36:36,840 --> 00:36:40,960
Right now, Poona is about to record
with Darathong Music!

424
00:36:41,040 --> 00:36:42,160
Yes.

425
00:36:42,760 --> 00:36:45,760
What? The competition just ended.
How is she already recording?

426
00:36:45,840 --> 00:36:48,040
The song is catchy. If it's released,

427
00:36:48,120 --> 00:36:50,200
it will definitely be a hit!

428
00:36:50,280 --> 00:36:52,000
- It will be number one!
- Yeah.

429
00:36:52,600 --> 00:36:53,800
Whoa!

430
00:36:53,880 --> 00:36:55,360
Dad, I won't allow it!

431
00:36:55,440 --> 00:36:58,360
Poona is going to be a singer!
I won't allow it!

432
00:36:58,440 --> 00:36:59,440
I won't allow it!

433
00:37:07,840 --> 00:37:11,280
Miss Maria. It's really upbeat!

434
00:37:12,680 --> 00:37:14,040
- Is that true?
- Yes.

435
00:37:22,520 --> 00:37:23,480
Hey! Stop right there!

436
00:37:30,000 --> 00:37:32,480
- You're really stupid for doing this.
- I don't care!

437
00:37:33,600 --> 00:37:35,200
If you take too long, the gun will go off!

438
00:37:57,600 --> 00:37:59,800
- Go wait outside.
- Yes, sir.

439
00:38:04,280 --> 00:38:05,440
Thank you so much, Village Head.

440
00:38:06,400 --> 00:38:08,600
If you hadn't helped me earlier,

441
00:38:09,440 --> 00:38:11,840
I would've been captured for sure.

442
00:38:11,920 --> 00:38:13,240
Don't worry about it, Boss.

443
00:38:13,320 --> 00:38:16,360
Actually, this is my job.

444
00:38:17,400 --> 00:38:20,400
But in the future, if you need anything,

445
00:38:20,480 --> 00:38:23,000
just let me know if I can be of service.

446
00:38:23,760 --> 00:38:24,960
Same here.

447
00:38:25,040 --> 00:38:28,920
If you need any help,
I'd like to repay your kindness.

448
00:38:29,520 --> 00:38:30,760
Just let me know.

449
00:38:34,280 --> 00:38:36,640
I do have one thing, Boss.

450
00:38:37,760 --> 00:38:41,240
My daughter dreams of becoming a singer.

451
00:38:41,320 --> 00:38:44,960
If it's not too much trouble…

452
00:38:47,200 --> 00:38:48,320
could you help her out?

453
00:38:59,200 --> 00:39:01,040
The night the explosion happened,

454
00:39:01,920 --> 00:39:06,320
Chit and his crew were to deliver drugs
to Pleaw, Boss Noo's man.

455
00:39:07,320 --> 00:39:09,560
But the police interfered,

456
00:39:09,640 --> 00:39:11,080
so the delivery didn't go through.

457
00:39:11,640 --> 00:39:12,920
Then what?

458
00:39:13,000 --> 00:39:17,040
Today, Boss Noo sent someone
to clear things up.

459
00:39:17,120 --> 00:39:20,200
Clear things up?
If we can't deliver the goods,

460
00:39:20,280 --> 00:39:23,800
we'll just reschedule.
What's the big deal? It's not a problem.

461
00:39:24,760 --> 00:39:28,080
But he suspects

462
00:39:28,160 --> 00:39:30,640
that we're working together
with the police.

463
00:39:30,720 --> 00:39:32,360
Well? Where are they?

464
00:39:34,760 --> 00:39:35,880
They're over there.

465
00:39:39,720 --> 00:39:43,280
Mr. Kitti, this is Pleaw,
Boss Noo's henchman.

466
00:39:46,000 --> 00:39:48,240
If you have something to say, just say it.

467
00:39:49,720 --> 00:39:51,360
Isn't Mr. Singha coming?

468
00:39:51,960 --> 00:39:54,000
This doesn't concern Mr. Singha.

469
00:39:54,720 --> 00:39:57,080
If you have something to say,
say it to me.

470
00:39:57,160 --> 00:39:59,640
Mr. Singha said he'd send
the goods to my boss,

471
00:40:00,400 --> 00:40:01,920
but it hasn't happened yet.

472
00:40:02,000 --> 00:40:03,880
Mr. Singha hasn't gone back on his word.

473
00:40:03,960 --> 00:40:06,680
But he's delayed sending the goods
several times now.

474
00:40:07,240 --> 00:40:08,800
We've already paid the deposit.

475
00:40:10,040 --> 00:40:13,120
This is clearly a scam.

476
00:40:13,640 --> 00:40:15,640
Pleaw, you're disrespecting my boss!

477
00:40:18,720 --> 00:40:20,280
Hey! Stop!

478
00:40:22,280 --> 00:40:24,400
Are you trying to kill each other?

479
00:40:24,480 --> 00:40:27,520
Just tell me
when you'll deliver the goods.

480
00:40:31,080 --> 00:40:32,480
Give me five days.

481
00:40:33,120 --> 00:40:35,280
You'll get the goods in five days.

482
00:40:37,840 --> 00:40:41,400
On the delivery day,
tell Mr. Singha to come.

483
00:40:42,400 --> 00:40:43,920
My boss wants to meet him.

484
00:40:45,000 --> 00:40:47,320
Fine. No problem.

485
00:40:55,080 --> 00:40:58,840
Mr. Kitti, I don't think
you should let them go like this.

486
00:41:05,680 --> 00:41:08,280
They're hoarding
precursor chemicals like this.

487
00:41:08,360 --> 00:41:09,800
KAMNAN PONG

488
00:41:09,880 --> 00:41:11,320
Should we raid them now, Captain?

489
00:41:11,400 --> 00:41:12,960
We can't raid them right now.

490
00:41:15,000 --> 00:41:16,560
This is a cleaning chemical.

491
00:41:16,640 --> 00:41:19,360
It's not illegal.
It's something everyone uses.

492
00:41:19,440 --> 00:41:21,800
But they're ordering hundreds of kilos,

493
00:41:21,880 --> 00:41:23,480
and now they're stockpiling it.

494
00:41:23,560 --> 00:41:26,880
This chemical can be used
to make methamphetamine, you know.

495
00:41:27,800 --> 00:41:29,400
If we raid now, they'll get away in court.

496
00:41:30,680 --> 00:41:33,120
We need more evidence
to tie them to the crime,

497
00:41:33,760 --> 00:41:37,080
like tracking the movement
of these chemicals

498
00:41:37,960 --> 00:41:39,200
until we find the source of the drugs.

499
00:41:40,480 --> 00:41:43,040
If we have coordinates, pictures,

500
00:41:43,760 --> 00:41:45,440
or videos, that would be great.

501
00:41:46,040 --> 00:41:47,000
So, where do we start?

502
00:41:49,440 --> 00:41:50,440
Sergeant Au.

503
00:41:51,320 --> 00:41:52,920
Do you know anything about Kitti?

504
00:41:57,680 --> 00:41:58,920
I know a bit.

505
00:42:02,160 --> 00:42:03,920
Kitti and Singha

506
00:42:04,000 --> 00:42:06,240
have been friends since 20 years ago.

507
00:42:07,360 --> 00:42:08,760
Back then, Singha

508
00:42:09,320 --> 00:42:11,360
was a singer for Kamnan Pong's label.

509
00:42:14,040 --> 00:42:17,800
But after the scandal
with the singer Phupha Thararin

510
00:42:18,600 --> 00:42:21,800
and Onanong Wongwichian
driving off a cliff and dying,

511
00:42:22,480 --> 00:42:23,920
Kamnan Pong was heartbroken.

512
00:42:25,520 --> 00:42:28,320
He let Singha handle the label.

513
00:42:30,640 --> 00:42:32,880
As for the other businesses,

514
00:42:32,960 --> 00:42:34,800
he let Kitti manage them.

515
00:42:34,880 --> 00:42:38,240
Later, Kitti ran for local politics

516
00:42:38,320 --> 00:42:40,960
and quietly became a powerful figure.

517
00:42:47,280 --> 00:42:49,760
Both of them
were Kamnan Pong's subordinates.

518
00:42:51,160 --> 00:42:52,080
Is it possible

519
00:42:52,160 --> 00:42:55,400
that Kamnan Pong is involved in this too?

520
00:42:56,240 --> 00:43:00,680
Kamnan Pong is known for supporting
the locals and fighting drugs.

521
00:43:02,240 --> 00:43:03,640
I don't think he's involved.

522
00:43:06,200 --> 00:43:07,760
We'll have to prove it with evidence.

523
00:43:08,840 --> 00:43:11,280
If the evidence points to him,
we can't let it go.

524
00:43:13,160 --> 00:43:15,480
For now, let's investigate Kitti first.

525
00:43:16,840 --> 00:43:19,720
Then we can expand from there.

526
00:43:20,680 --> 00:43:22,200
- Understood.
- Understood.

527
00:43:22,280 --> 00:43:23,560
CONSTRUCTION SITE

528
00:43:25,520 --> 00:43:26,640
In five days?

529
00:43:28,320 --> 00:43:31,040
Yes, but don't worry.

530
00:43:32,040 --> 00:43:34,000
We'll definitely send them the goods.

531
00:43:34,560 --> 00:43:35,920
Forget the delivery.

532
00:43:36,800 --> 00:43:37,960
Let's cut ties with them.

533
00:43:38,960 --> 00:43:40,720
Sounds good, Singha.

534
00:43:42,880 --> 00:43:44,320
But we need to be cautious.

535
00:43:45,440 --> 00:43:47,040
Boss Noo, that man.

536
00:43:48,160 --> 00:43:49,600
He can't be trusted.

537
00:43:51,600 --> 00:43:55,240
Don't worry about that. I'll handle it.

538
00:44:03,240 --> 00:44:05,360
DARATHONG MUSIC

539
00:44:08,840 --> 00:44:13,120
Teacher, I'm so excited!
I'm finally going to record.

540
00:44:13,200 --> 00:44:15,360
Calm down.

541
00:44:15,440 --> 00:44:18,600
Take a deep breath.

542
00:44:18,680 --> 00:44:20,880
Today you're recording,

543
00:44:20,960 --> 00:44:24,040
and you're officially going to be
a singer now!

544
00:44:25,360 --> 00:44:27,160
- I'll do my best!
- Good!

545
00:44:28,760 --> 00:44:29,880
- Alright, let's go.
- Let's go!

546
00:44:29,960 --> 00:44:32,160
DARATHONG MUSIC

547
00:44:35,480 --> 00:44:37,120
- Hello.
- Hello.

548
00:44:38,320 --> 00:44:40,080
I've brought a new singer here to record.

549
00:44:41,400 --> 00:44:44,480
- You're Miss Poona, right?
- Yes, it's me, Poona.

550
00:44:45,720 --> 00:44:50,320
The management asked me to inform you
that the recording is canceled for today.

551
00:44:55,080 --> 00:44:56,920
What happened? Just the other day,

552
00:44:57,000 --> 00:45:00,720
they had her practice
and send the recording to Mr. Singha.

553
00:45:00,800 --> 00:45:03,840
Mr. Singha himself scheduled today

554
00:45:03,920 --> 00:45:05,320
for us to record.

555
00:45:05,920 --> 00:45:09,680
I really don't know about this.
Mr. Singha just told me this.

556
00:45:12,160 --> 00:45:13,800
Can I meet Mr. Singha?

557
00:45:14,480 --> 00:45:16,800
Mr. Singha is unavailable today.

558
00:45:29,880 --> 00:45:33,280
Teacher, is that my song?

559
00:45:34,200 --> 00:45:37,320
- Let's go check.
- You can't go up there.

560
00:45:37,400 --> 00:45:40,000
You can't go in. Excuse me!

561
00:45:40,080 --> 00:45:42,520
You can't go in! Hey!

562
00:45:43,040 --> 00:45:47,840
<i>Who owns this famous music label?</i>
<i>They say the boss is good-looking</i>

563
00:45:47,920 --> 00:45:54,000
<i>The singers of this label are all handsome</i>
<i>And famous, at the top level</i>

564
00:45:54,080 --> 00:45:58,600
<i>I want to be famous, I want to try</i>
<i>I want to be one of the artists</i>

565
00:45:58,680 --> 00:46:02,480
<i>At this label, I want to be famous</i>

566
00:46:02,560 --> 00:46:07,320
<i>Can't stand it anymore, I want people</i>
<i>To scream for me at the stage</i>

567
00:46:07,400 --> 00:46:09,160
<i>Please accept me as an artist</i>

568
00:46:18,840 --> 00:46:22,280
Wasn't anyone told
that your recording today was cancelled?

569
00:46:22,880 --> 00:46:24,920
I did inform them, but…

570
00:46:29,880 --> 00:46:31,640
What's going on?

571
00:46:33,040 --> 00:46:34,000
Why…

572
00:46:34,960 --> 00:46:38,120
Why is Maria singing my song?

573
00:46:45,000 --> 00:46:46,440
- Ice.
- Yes?

574
00:46:46,520 --> 00:46:48,360
Take Poona out. I need to work.

575
00:46:48,440 --> 00:46:49,960
Okay.

576
00:46:50,040 --> 00:46:51,400
Teacher, let's go outside.

577
00:47:11,760 --> 00:47:12,760
Well…

578
00:47:16,800 --> 00:47:18,120
I apologize

579
00:47:19,120 --> 00:47:21,920
for the sudden change,
but it's due to suitability concerns.

580
00:47:23,320 --> 00:47:25,080
Does that mean I'm not suitable?

581
00:47:25,680 --> 00:47:28,520
- Well…
- Poona won the competition.

582
00:47:28,600 --> 00:47:32,000
She won first place and signed a contract
to become a singer with the label.

583
00:47:33,000 --> 00:47:36,160
The label gave her a song to practice
until she mastered it.

584
00:47:36,240 --> 00:47:39,120
How exactly is she unsuitable?
Could you explain?

585
00:47:41,680 --> 00:47:44,040
Well, Teacher…

586
00:47:44,720 --> 00:47:48,400
This song has a rhythm,
and it requires both singing and dancing.

587
00:47:50,960 --> 00:47:53,000
My father also saw that…

588
00:47:54,880 --> 00:47:56,880
Maria is more suitable for this role.

589
00:47:57,640 --> 00:47:59,960
But I can sing and dance too.

590
00:48:00,040 --> 00:48:02,560
Yes, that's true. You can sing and dance.

591
00:48:02,640 --> 00:48:05,960
But it's not natural for you.

592
00:48:06,560 --> 00:48:10,520
It's not part of your character.
For a song these days to be successful,

593
00:48:10,600 --> 00:48:15,360
it must come from the artist's feelings,
from the singer themselves.

594
00:48:17,240 --> 00:48:20,880
This song doesn't fully showcase
your potential

595
00:48:20,960 --> 00:48:22,000
or bring out the best in you.

596
00:48:25,680 --> 00:48:28,320
Poona, I believe you can do it.
You can sing.

597
00:48:29,200 --> 00:48:31,320
But this song just isn't right for you.

598
00:48:32,040 --> 00:48:33,440
Don't worry, Poona.

599
00:48:34,440 --> 00:48:35,960
Even though this song didn't work out,

600
00:48:36,560 --> 00:48:38,480
I promise

601
00:48:38,560 --> 00:48:40,960
I'll find a new one for you.

602
00:48:41,480 --> 00:48:43,160
And you'll definitely make it.

603
00:48:44,960 --> 00:48:47,040
How long will she have to wait?

604
00:48:50,880 --> 00:48:53,280
A couple of months.

605
00:48:53,880 --> 00:48:56,480
A couple of months?

606
00:48:56,560 --> 00:48:59,120
What am I supposed to do while I wait?

607
00:49:00,400 --> 00:49:02,920
I won't take advantage of you, Poona.

608
00:49:04,600 --> 00:49:05,880
While waiting for the new song,

609
00:49:06,960 --> 00:49:11,600
I'll have you work as an intern
at the company.

610
00:49:17,680 --> 00:49:19,000
Is that a good idea, Poona?

611
00:49:19,080 --> 00:49:21,160
Your talent is singing,

612
00:49:21,240 --> 00:49:22,960
not working in an office.

613
00:49:34,560 --> 00:49:36,000
Wait!

614
00:49:36,880 --> 00:49:38,240
Who are you?

615
00:49:38,320 --> 00:49:41,440
What's your role in the company?

616
00:49:41,520 --> 00:49:42,760
Costume!

617
00:49:42,840 --> 00:49:45,760
If you can't afford food,
don't be shy, okay?

618
00:49:45,840 --> 00:49:48,000
I'll help you out.

619
00:49:48,080 --> 00:49:49,320
No!

620
00:49:51,160 --> 00:49:52,880
NEXT EPISODE

621
00:51:52,840 --> 00:51:55,760
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
